---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="How This Site Is Supported"
	description="No display ads. Honest affiliate links. Digital products from real family life. Here's how Darbees Chasing Rainbows is supported."
>
	<article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 md:py-24">
		<!-- Hero -->
		<div class="mb-16 text-center md:mb-20">
			<div
				class="bg-primary/10 text-primary mb-6 inline-flex h-16 w-16 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl"
			>
				<svg
					xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
					class="h-8 w-8"
					viewBox="0 0 20 20"
					fill="currentColor"
				>
					<path
						fill-rule="evenodd"
						d="M6.267 3.455a3.066 3.066 0 001.745-.723 3.066 3.066 0 013.976 0 3.066 3.066 0 001.745.723 3.066 3.066 0 012.812 2.812c.051.643.304 1.254.723 1.745a3.066 3.066 0 010 3.976 3.066 3.066 0 00-.723 1.745 3.066 3.066 0 01-2.812 2.812 3.066 3.066 0 00-1.745.723 3.066 3.066 0 01-3.976 0 3.066 3.066 0 00-1.745-.723 3.066 3.066 0 01-2.812-2.812 3.066 3.066 0 00-.723-1.745 3.066 3.066 0 010-3.976 3.066 3.066 0 00.723-1.745 3.066 3.066 0 012.812-2.812zm7.44 5.252a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z"
						clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
				</svg>
			</div>
			<h1 class="font-display mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold md:text-5xl">
				How This Site Is Supported
			</h1>
			<p class="text-base-content/70 mx-auto max-w-2xl text-lg md:text-xl">
				We want this site to stay useful, calm, honest, and uncluttered. Here's what that looks like
				in practice.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Core principle -->
		<div class="border-primary/20 bg-primary/5 mb-16 rounded-3xl border p-8 text-center md:p-10">
			<p class="font-display text-base-content mb-2 text-xl font-bold">
				"We try to monetize the resources, not the relationship."
			</p>
			<p class="text-base-content/70 text-sm">
				The blog should stay clean and readable. Monetization belongs where it naturally helps the
				reader.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- No display ads -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg mb-10 max-w-none">
			<h2>No display ads</h2>
			<p>
				This site does not use display advertising. We don't want banner ads, popups, or
				auto-playing content cluttering the reading experience or promoting things we haven't chosen
				to recommend. We want the site to feel calm and trustworthy — and display ads work against
				that.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Affiliate links -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg mb-10 max-w-none">
			<h2>Affiliate links</h2>
			<p>
				Some links on this site may be affiliate links. If you click a link and make a purchase, we
				may receive a small commission at no extra cost to you.
			</p>
			<p>
				Our rule: we only link to things we actually use, have used, or would recommend to a family
				we know personally. We don't do generic roundups of gear we've never touched. Reviews
				include downsides as well as upsides. Affiliate relationships are always disclosed.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Digital products -->
		<div class="border-base-300 bg-base-100 mb-16 rounded-2xl border p-8">
			<h2 class="font-display mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Digital products</h2>
			<p class="text-base-content/80 mb-4">
				We create homeschool resources, field notes templates, book discernment tools, RV
				checklists, and project guides — built from real family life, not generic worksheets. These
				are field-tested in an actual RV homeschool with four kids.
			</p>
			<p class="text-base-content/80">
				Products are available through the <a href="/resources" class="text-primary hover:underline"
					>Resources</a
				> page. Free resources are offered as lead magnets to build the newsletter list. Paid resources
				are priced to be accessible.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- YouTube -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg mb-10 max-w-none">
			<h2>YouTube</h2>
			<p>
				YouTube is a companion format to blog posts — not a replacement for them. Videos for
				projects, field notes, homeschool rhythms, and Kingdom Farm updates will live alongside
				written posts and full documentation. The blog is the archive; YouTube is the window.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Sponsors -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg mb-10 max-w-none">
			<h2>Sponsors</h2>
			<p>
				We may work with sponsors in the future. If we do, sponsors must be values-aligned —
				companies we would be comfortable recommending to families we know personally. We would not
				sponsor anything that conflicts with our faith, family values, or the honest posture of the
				site. Sponsored content will always be clearly labeled.
			</p>
			<p>
				Good categories: homeschool tools, books, RV gear, outdoor gear, farming tools, food
				preservation, practical maker tools. Poor fits: random apps, fear-based products,
				low-quality preparedness brands, anything requiring health claims we can't verify.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Support / Donations -->
		<div class="border-base-300 bg-base-100 mb-16 rounded-2xl border p-8">
			<h2 class="font-display mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Direct support</h2>
			<p class="text-base-content/80 mb-4">
				Some readers have asked how to support the journey directly. We're grateful for that.
			</p>
			<p class="text-base-content/80 mb-4">
				For now, the most meaningful support is: subscribe to the newsletter, share the site with
				someone who'd find it useful, and follow along on Instagram. That does more than most people
				realize.
			</p>
			<p class="text-base-content/80 mb-4">
				If we open a formal support channel for Kingdom Farm, it will be tied to specific
				milestones, fully transparent about how funds are used, and free of pressure. We will never
				use "investment" language or make promises we cannot keep. Support is support — not a
				transaction.
			</p>
			<p class="text-base-content/60 text-sm italic">No support program is currently active.</p>
		</div>

		<!-- How We Share -->
		<div class="bg-base-200 mb-16 rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-10">
			<h2 class="font-display mb-6 text-2xl font-bold">How we share</h2>
			<ul class="text-base-content/80 space-y-3">
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">→</span>
					<span>We tell the truth, but not everything.</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">→</span>
					<span
						>We protect our children. No faces, no private moments, no content that makes them the
						product.</span
					>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">→</span>
					<span>We do not use fear to sell.</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">→</span>
					<span>We do not make health, legal, or financial claims we cannot back up.</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">→</span>
					<span>We correct mistakes publicly when we get things wrong.</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">→</span>
					<span>We do not overpromise. What we can do, we'll do. What we can't, we'll say so.</span>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<!-- Closing -->
		<div class="text-center">
			<p class="text-base-content/70 mb-6">
				Questions about any of this? <a href="/contact" class="text-primary hover:underline"
					>Get in touch.</a
				>
			</p>
			<div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
				<a href="/about" class="btn btn-outline btn-sm">Our Story</a>
				<a href="/resources" class="btn btn-outline btn-sm">Resources</a>
				<a href="/start-here" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">Start Here</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</article>
</BaseLayout>
